'''Barry S. Anton''' is an American psychologist. He served as the president of the [[American Psychological Association]] (APA) in 2015.
==Biography== Anton earned a Ph.D. from [[Colorado State University]]. He is a distinguished professor emeritus at the [[University of Puget Sound]] and is in the private practice of clinical psychology in [[Tacoma, Washington]].<ref name=APA/> He spent more than 30 years the University of Puget Sound.<ref name="UPS">{{cite web|title=Barry S. Anton|url=http://www.pugetsound.edu/about/offices-services/university-relations/donor-relations/named-sites-on-campus/barry-anton/|publisher=[[University of Puget Sound]]|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref> He was the co-author of a textbook, ''Introduction to Clinical Psychology''.<ref name="Brodsky">{{cite journal|last1=Brodsky|first1=Annette|last2=Steinberg-Oren|first2=Susan|title=Clinical psychology: Insider edition|journal=[[PsycCRITIQUES]]|date=2008|volume=53|issue=28|url=http://psycnet.apa.org/index.cfm?fa=buy.optionToBuy&uid=2008-05965-001|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref>
In 1997, Anton received the Karl F. Heiser APA Presidential Award for Advocacy.<ref name="Heiser">{{cite web|title=Karl F. Heiser APA Presidential Award for Advocacy|url=http://www.apadivisions.org/division-31/awards/heiser.aspx?tab=4|publisher=[[American Psychological Association]]|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref> After serving on several APA task forces, Anton became president-elect in 2014 and APA president in 2015.<ref name="APA">{{cite web|title=American Psychological Association elects University of Puget Sound professor Barry S. Anton as 2015 president|url=http://www.apa.org/news/press/releases/2013/11/barry-anton.aspx|publisher=[[American Psychological Association]]|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref> Anton said that a focus of his presidency would be future opportunities for early-career psychologists.<ref name="WSPA">{{cite web|title=Changing career landscape Is focus for Anton as APA president|url=http://www.wapsych.org/news/153671/Changing-Career-Landscape-Is-Focus-for-Anton-as-APA-President.htm|publisher=Washington State Psychological Association|accessdate=December 13, 2016}}</ref>
