{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = {{lang|fi|Kansaneläkelaitos}} |logo = Kela suomi kela-1-.jpg |logo_width = 220px |logo_caption = Kela |formed = December 16, 1937 |jurisdiction = [[Finland]] |headquarters = [[Helsinki]] |employees = 6,092 (December 31, 2010) |budget = 12.6 billion € (2010) |chief1_name = [[Elli Aaltonen]] |chief1_position = Director General |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = [[Parliament of Finland]] |website = {{Url|https://www.kela.fi/web/en}} |footnotes = }} '''Kela''', abbr. from {{lang-fi|Kansaneläkelaitos}}, {{lang-sv|Folkpensionsanstalten}} (Fpa), {{lang-en|The Social Insurance Institution}} (SII), is a [[Finland|Finnish]] government agency in charge of settling benefits under national [[Social security in Finland|social security]] programs. Kela was founded in 1937 to handle [[retirement pay]]. In the 1980s and 1990s, its role was expanded to handle other fields like [[child benefit]]s, [[unemployment benefit]]s, [[Health benefits (insurance)|sickness benefit]]s, [[health insurance]] and [[Student financial aid (Finland)|student financial aid]].
Kela is funded from compulsory payments to some of the administered schemes (24 % 2015)<ref>[http://www.kela.fi/documents/10180/1169692/Kelan_toimintakertomus_2015.pdf Toimintakertomus 2015] (Finnish)</ref> and by [[taxation]]. Coverage under the schemes is given to all permanent residents of Finland. ''Kansaneläkelaitos/Folkpensionsanstalten'' literally means "People's Pension Institute", reflecting its original function as the national provider of retirement benefits.
